        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer145297275" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16570535087867168178">Whatever name she&apos;s writing under, Krentz&apos;s books are among my favorite guilty pleasures. Formulaic - you bet! Do I care - nope! When I want a happy ending with fun verbal sparring, the unconventional heroine, the brooding alpha male, I know I can pick up a Krentz novel and be happy, no matter how many times I&apos;ve read the story before (and after a while, they can start running together). Except for this one. <br/><br/>It lost me when I found out that Mattie declared her love for Hugh and begged him to mar</span>
  <span id="freeText16570535087867168178" style="display:none">Whatever name she's writing under, Krentz's books are among my favorite guilty pleasures. Formulaic - you bet! Do I care - nope! When I want a happy ending with fun verbal sparring, the unconventional heroine, the brooding alpha male, I know I can pick up a Krentz novel and be happy, no matter how many times I've read the story before (and after a while, they can start running together). Except for this one. <br /><br />It lost me when I found out that Mattie declared her love for Hugh and begged him to marry her THE DAY HER SISTER BROKE OFF THEIR ENGAGEMENT! (Yep - she went after her sister's ex-fiance.) Then she gets pissed because he said no. Really? I lost all respect for the character and had no idea why Hugh changed his mind. <br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="16570535087867168178" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
