<span id="freeTextContainer6172644325868686617">This was the first JAK I ever read and as such it is special to me. It has everything I expect - an original heroine with family issues, an alpha hero with an old score to settle and some interesting secondary characters. <br/><br/>I like the idea of St. Gabe, especially once it gets a tiny bit more mainstream. <a class='jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction'>(view spoiler)</a><span class='spoilerContainer' style='display: none'>[Sounds like it will be fun between Mattie&apos;s new business, Silk&apos;s painting and Evangeline&apos;s dresses <a class='jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction'>(hide spoiler)</a>]</span></span>
  <span id="freeText6172644325868686617" style="display:none">This was the first JAK I ever read and as such it is special to me. It has everything I expect - an original heroine with family issues, an alpha hero with an old score to settle and some interesting secondary characters. <br /><br />I like the idea of St. Gabe, especially once it gets a tiny bit more mainstream. <a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[Sounds like it will be fun between Mattie's new business, Silk's painting and Evangeline's dresses <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span></span>
