<span id="freeTextContainer13179848818451347906">Early 90&apos;s Jayne Ann Krentz novels had some pretty domineering and arrogant heroes, and this one is no different. I must&apos;ve enjoyed that then because that&apos;s when I bought this book. It&apos;s not as entertaining now, but it&apos;s a way to pass a rainy afternoon with a cup of tea.</span>
  <span id="freeText13179848818451347906" style="display:none">Early 90's Jayne Ann Krentz novels had some pretty domineering and arrogant heroes, and this one is no different. I must've enjoyed that then because that's when I bought this book. It's not as entertaining now, but it's a way to pass a rainy afternoon with a cup of tea.</span>
